definition.value: Variation in ATP11A, which resides in the chromosome region linked to this disease, 13q34, has been shown to cause autosomal dominant nonsyndromic deafness but evidence does not support it as the cause of this subtype. Reassessment of the haplotype for this disease has suggested that the locus may be inaccurate [JAB].
